<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · The kitchen is a system, not a single appliance</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">A premium outdoor kitchen is rarely just a grill.</h2>

    <p>A finished outdoor kitchen in Beverly Hills or Newport Beach is rarely just a grill. It's a built-in cooking line: grill at the center, side burners flanking it, a sear station or power burner on one side, a warming drawer below, refrigerator drawers under the counter, an ice maker built into the bar end, a pizza oven in the wall, vent hood overhead, sink at the prep zone. $40,000 on the low end. $250,000 in the Hidden Hills builds we see.</p>

    <p>When something fails, it's rarely just one thing. The pattern: a side burner stops lighting and the homeowner doesn't notice until they have a dinner party three weeks later, by which point the warming drawer has also developed an issue and the outdoor refrigerator's gasket is letting warm air in. Three small problems become one expensive call because nobody was using the patio kitchen daily during winter.</p>

    <p>We service the whole ecosystem. Grills get their own page (see <a href="/outdoor/grill-repair/">built-in grill repair</a>). This page covers everything else. Side burners, warming drawers, outdoor refrigerators, pizza ovens, vent hoods, ice makers, the integrated systems. EPA 608 certified for refrigerant components. CSLB #1138898.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 COMPONENT BREAKDOWN -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Component breakdown</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we service across the kitchen.</h2>

    <div class="component-block">
      <h3>Side Burners (Lynx, Fire Magic, DCS, Twin Eagles, Wolf Outdoor, Hestan, Alfresco, Kalamazoo)</h3>
      <p>Side burners on built-in outdoor kitchens fail like residential cooktops. Orifice blocked from cooking spillover, igniter clicks but no spark (battery), gas regulator drift at the supply line. We see Lynx side burners and sear stations most often (LSB1-1, LSB2-1, LCB1-1 ProSear). Common failure: the burner valve seizes after long inactive periods. Winter unused, then summer comes and won't open. Disassemble, clean, lubricate, retest. $200 to $380 typical.</p>
      <p>Power burners (Lynx ProSear, Fire Magic Echelon Power Burner, Twin Eagles 27,000 BTU side) run hot enough that the burner head itself burns out at 5 to 7 years. Replacement runs $400 to $700 depending on brand.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="component-block">
      <h3>Warming Drawers (Wolf WWD30, Lynx LWD30, DCS WD30, Twin Eagles TEWD30)</h3>
      <p>Warming drawer failures fall into three buckets. (1) Heating element failure: element open-circuits, drawer doesn't heat. $250 to $380 element plus labor. (2) Controller board failure: drawer runs but won't hold setpoint. $400 to $650 controller plus labor. (3) Drawer slide mechanism: runners corrode in marine environments, drawer doesn't open smoothly. $180 to $280 hardware plus labor.</p>
      <p>Wolf WWD30 outdoor uses the same controller architecture as the indoor Wolf warming drawer (we know this brand inside and out). Lynx LWD30 has a more straightforward control system, easier diagnosis.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="component-block">
      <h3>Outdoor Refrigerators &amp; Beverage Centers</h3>
      <p>Sub-Zero outdoor 424 series, U-Line outdoor, Perlick HP24 / HP15, Lynx LM24REFL, Hestan GFR24, True Residential outdoor, Viking outdoor, Wolf Outdoor. Outdoor-rated refrigerators are not just regular fridges in a cabinet. They have sealed-system specs, gasket compounds, and condenser placements built for high ambient temps and humidity swings. EPA 608 required for any refrigerant work, and we have it.</p>
      <p>Common failures we see, in order:</p>
      <ol class="ord-list">
        <li><strong>Condenser fan motor seized</strong> at 4 to 7 years. Outdoor units accumulate dust load faster than indoor. Replacement $280 to $450 depending on brand.</li>
        <li><strong>Door gasket compressed flat.</strong> Won't seal in summer heat. Replacement $180 to $340.</li>
        <li><strong>Evaporator drain blocked.</strong> Water pools, freezes, blocks airflow. Cleaning plus drain heater check.</li>
        <li><strong>Compressor short-cycling on heat.</strong> Usually condenser coil fouled. Cleaning solves 60% of these without parts.</li>
        <li><strong>Compressor failure</strong> at 8 to 12 years. Replacement $1,200 to $2,200. At this price, replace-vs-repair becomes a real conversation.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="component-block">
      <h3>Outdoor Ice Makers (Lynx LM-15, Hestan GICR15, Sub-Zero IC-15RE, U-Line BI-2115, Scotsman SCN60 outdoor)</h3>
      <p>Outdoor ice makers fail more often than indoor. Heat load plus humidity plus dust. Common: water inlet valve at the wall (calcium buildup in SoCal hard water), drain pump (debris from condenser drip), sensor fouling. Most repairs $300 to $650. The Scotsman SCN60 outdoor specifically: we see condenser coil fouling at the 3-year mark. Clean it, runs another 4 years easy.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="component-block">
      <h3>Pizza Ovens, Outdoor Gas (Mugnaini gas, Forno Bravo gas, Alfresco AXEPZA, Lynx LPZA, Kalamazoo Outdoor Pizza)</h3>
      <p>Gas-fired outdoor pizza ovens, we service these. Most common: regulator failure (the high-BTU output stresses the regulator), igniter sequence failure on the dual-burner Mugnaini and Forno Bravo gas conversions, deck stone crack from thermal shock (replacement $150 to $340).</p>
      <p>We don't service wood-fired pizza ovens (chimney/masonry trade) or pellet ovens. Gas-fired only.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="component-block">
      <h3>Vent Hoods (Vent-A-Hood outdoor B100 / B200, Best WCB6, Trade-Wind L7242, custom outdoor hoods)</h3>
      <p>Outdoor vent hood failures: blower motor (4 to 8 years), light fixture corrosion (LED outdoor-rated still fails near salt water in 5 to 7 years), control switch pitting. Vent-A-Hood B-series uses the same blower architecture as indoor. Parts available, repair straightforward.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="component-block">
      <h3>Outdoor Sink Hardware</h3>
      <p>We don't do plumbing, that's a different trade. We do replace failed faucet hardware (the fixture itself, not the supply lines) when it's part of a larger outdoor kitchen service call. Outdoor-rated faucets corrode at 7 to 12 years even on premium brands. We can swap a faucet during a kitchen service visit if you have the replacement on hand.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="component-block">
      <h3>Integration Failures</h3>
      <p>Sometimes the issue isn't a single component. We've diagnosed:</p>
      <ul class="bullet-list">
        <li>Three appliances simultaneously underperforming. Root cause was gas pressure drop at the regulator serving the whole kitchen (low pressure = poor combustion across all burners + pilot light issues on warming drawer + ice maker cycling problems).</li>
        <li>Multiple electrical components failing. Root cause was outdoor receptacle GFCI tripping intermittently from water intrusion, leaving warming drawer and ice maker on partial power.</li>
        <li>Refrigerator + ice maker both running warm. Both shared a condensate drain line that had clogged.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>These multi-component diagnoses are where SDAR earns the higher service call. Single-component shops would charge for three visits.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 DIAGNOSTIC PROCESS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Diagnostic process for outdoor kitchens</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">When the call is "multiple things not working," here's the order.</h2>

    <ol class="diag-list">
      <li><strong>Master gas pressure check</strong> at the kitchen's main regulator. Should match spec for total BTU load (10 to 13" WC for natural gas premium kitchen builds). Low pressure means everything underperforms.</li>
      <li><strong>Master electrical check.</strong> GFCI status, outlet voltage, dedicated circuit breakers. Outdoor receptacles trip more than indoor.</li>
      <li><strong>Component-by-component test.</strong> Each burner, each appliance, each function. We make a list, present it to the homeowner, prioritize by importance.</li>
      <li><strong>Refrigeration system check</strong> if applicable. Temperature stability, condenser coil cleanliness, gasket integrity.</li>
      <li><strong>Vent hood draft test.</strong> Make sure exhaust is actually working. Fans run but blockage is common.</li>
      <li><strong>Repair sequence planning.</strong> If multiple repairs needed, we sequence them to minimize follow-up visits.</li>
    </ol>

    <p>A typical outdoor kitchen full diagnostic takes 60 to 90 minutes. We charge the standard $120 diagnostic regardless of how many components are tested.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 REAL REPAIR STORIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04 · Real repair stories</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Recent jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Composite examples; model numbers, ages, and prices reflect typical scope.</p>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Hidden Hills · complete Lynx outdoor kitchen, 2019 install</h3>
      <p>8-burner grill + 2x side burners + warming drawer + refrigerator + ice maker. Owner called because "the grill side won't light." Arrived, ran full kitchen diagnostic. Findings: (1) Left side burner (Lynx LSB1-1) orifice clogged with grease drippings. (2) Warming drawer (Lynx LWD30) drawer slide corroded, opens but binds. (3) Outdoor refrigerator (Lynx LM24REFL) door gasket compressed flat, ambient cabinet temp 4°F warm. (4) Ice maker fine, no issue. Repaired LSB orifice (clean only, no parts), replaced warming drawer slide hardware, replaced refrigerator gasket. Total: $120 diag + $340 parts + 3 hours = $740. One visit. Customer's previous shop had quoted three separate service calls.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Beverly Hills · Sub-Zero 424 outdoor refrigerator, 7 years old</h3>
      <p>Not cooling, ambient 92°F outside. Condenser fan motor seized, common at 5 to 7 years on outdoor units due to dust load. Replaced fan motor, cleaned condenser coil, tested. Pulldown to 38°F in 3 hours. Total: $120 + $385 part + 1 hour = $620.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Calabasas · Mugnaini Wood Fire Oven gas-converted, 2017 conversion</h3>
      <p>Ignition sequence failed mid-cook. Diagnosed: secondary burner igniter glow rod failed. Replacement glow rod $180 part, 45-minute install. Tested ignition cycle 5x. Working. Total: $120 + $180 + $90 labor = $390.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Pacific Palisades · multi-component failure call</h3>
      <p>Warming drawer cold, refrigerator warm, ice maker not making ice, all simultaneously. Diagnosed: outdoor GFCI receptacle had tripped from water intrusion during last rainy week. Three appliances all on the same circuit. Reset GFCI, tested, all working. Identified water intrusion source (mortar gap above receptacle), recommended caulk repair. Charged $120 diagnostic only. Customer requested annual maintenance contract.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Newport Beach · Wolf Outdoor warming drawer (WWD30), 4 years old</h3>
      <p>Element failure. Tested element: open circuit. Replaced Wolf element kit. Total: $120 + $310 part + 1 hour = $510. Wolf parts are excellent quality but pricier than Lynx equivalents.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 HONEST SCOPE -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05 · Honest scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we service, what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong> all major built-in outdoor kitchen brands and components. Lynx, Fire Magic, DCS, Twin Eagles, Alfresco, Kalamazoo, Wolf Outdoor, Viking Outdoor, Hestan, Napoleon, Coyote, Blaze, Bull, Summerset, RCS, American Outdoor Grill. Side burners, sear stations, power burners, warming drawers, outdoor refrigerators (EPA 608 certified), outdoor ice makers, gas-fired pizza ovens, vent hoods, faucet hardware swap during service calls.</p>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="scope-list">
      <li><strong>New outdoor kitchen construction or expansion.</strong> We partner with several Beverly Hills, Calabasas, and Newport Beach outdoor kitchen contractors and can refer.</li>
      <li><strong>Plumbing supply lines, gas line installation from the meter.</strong> Plumber trade. We work with outdoor-experienced plumbers in each county.</li>
      <li><strong>Wood-fired pizza ovens or wood-burning fire features.</strong> SCAQMD Rule 445 restricts these in most of SoCal anyway. Gas conversion is what we do.</li>
      <li><strong>Pool and spa equipment.</strong> Different trade. We refer.</li>
      <li><strong>Outdoor lighting, audio, irrigation systems.</strong> Different trades.</li>
      <li><strong>Custom cabinetry repair.</strong> Stainless cabinetry replacement panels are a metal fabricator job, not appliance repair.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Premium homeowners and property managers value contractors who refer to specialists rather than fake competence outside their license.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 PRICING -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">06 · Pricing</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What outdoor kitchen repair actually costs.</h2>

    <table class="price-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Repair</th><th>Typical cost</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Diagnostic</td><td>$120, waived with repair</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Side burner cleaning / orifice</td><td>$200 to $380</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Side burner replacement</td><td>$400 to $700</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Power burner / sear station replacement</td><td>$500 to $900</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Warming drawer element</td><td>$370 to $550</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Warming drawer controller</td><td>$520 to $850</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Outdoor refrigerator fan motor</td><td>$400 to $620</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Outdoor refrigerator gasket</td><td>$260 to $450</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Outdoor refrigerator full compressor</td><td>$1,200 to $2,200</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Outdoor ice maker repair</td><td>$300 to $650</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Pizza oven igniter / regulator</td><td>$290 to $520</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Vent hood blower motor</td><td>$380 to $600</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Multi-component diagnostic (full kitchen)</td><td>$120 (single charge)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Warranty</td><td>90 days parts + labor</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p class="price-note">If you have multiple component issues, we diagnose and quote the whole picture before any repairs. You decide what to fix and in what order. Sometimes deferring the $1,800 compressor on the outdoor refrigerator and replacing it next season makes financial sense. We'll tell you that.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 07 WHY US -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">07 · Why customers call us back</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Eight reasons.</h2>

    <ul class="why-list">
      <li><strong>Whole-kitchen approach.</strong> We diagnose the system, not just one component. Multi-issue calls are our specialty.</li>
      <li><strong>EPA 608 certified.</strong> Required for any outdoor refrigerator or ice maker work involving refrigerant. See our <a href="/credentials/epa-certified/">EPA certification page</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Brand expertise across the ecosystem.</strong> Lynx + Wolf + Sub-Zero + Vent-A-Hood, we know all of these, not just one.</li>
      <li><strong>Coastal salt expertise.</strong> Malibu, Newport Beach, Pacific Palisades make up 40% of our outdoor kitchen calls. We know which parts fail near saltwater and stock accordingly.</li>
      <li><strong>Gas pressure diagnostics.</strong> Most outdoor kitchen "everything is broken" calls turn out to be one upstream issue. We test for it first.</li>
      <li><strong>Parts on the van.</strong> Lynx side burners, common warming drawer elements, outdoor refrigerator gaskets, condenser fan motors, common ignition components.</li>
      <li><strong>Honest replace-vs-repair on aging units.</strong> A 12-year-old outdoor refrigerator with compressor failure is a replace conversation. We say so.</li>
      <li><strong>CSLB #1138898 + BBB A+.</strong> Same-day across LA, OC, Ventura. Phones answered 24/7.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>For grill-only service see <a href="/outdoor/grill-repair/">built-in grill repair</a>. Sibling outdoor services: <a href="/outdoor/patio-heater-repair/">patio heater repair</a> and <a href="/outdoor/fireplace-repair/">outdoor fireplace repair</a>. Parent hub: <a href="/outdoor/">outdoor appliance repair overview</a>. For indoor refrigerator service (different scope, $89 residential diagnostic): <a href="/services/refrigerator-repair/">residential refrigerator repair</a>. LA County coverage detail: <a href="/los-angeles-county/">LA County service page</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

